wikipedia_page.main: Charles Henry Templeton (24 November 1806 – 2 March 1834) was an English cricketer with amateur status. He was associated with Cambridge University and Kent and made his first-class debut in 1827. He was educated at Winchester College and Trinity College, Cambridge.
